node.text:
Are you ready to dance again? Here, famed dancers Melissa Verdecia, Calvin Royal III, Xin Ying, Misty Copeland, Savion Glover, Stella Abrera, Vinson Fraley, Lloyd Knight, Courtney Celeste Spears, Tatiana Desardouin, and Tiler Peck showcase each of their individual style and expression of dance.

Featuring: @mmelifern @calvinroyaliii @xin_ying_dance @mistyonpointe the_savionglover @stellaabreradetsky @heyvinson @lloydknight @bahamaballerina @tatianadesardouin @tilerpeck

Director + Director of Photography: @mr_dume
Stylist: @samiranasr
Producers: @kriceee @imurillo
Assistant Camera: @forthexperience
Editor: @mr_dume
Colorist: @ericaharperdillman
Motion Designer: @annaaaiello
Entertainment Director: @angcutt

node.title: Misty Copeland, Savion Glover & More World-Class Dancers Are Back on Stage

Our August cover star @GigiHadid embarks on her dream cake-baking internship under #CakeBoss's own @BuddyValastro, the prolific baker of cakes best known for his impressive larger-than-life cake designs. Here, Gigi talks cooking and baking with her family on the farm, everything bagel pregnancy cravings, and favorite ‘Cake Boss’ moments.

The real turning point in Samara Weaving’s (@samweaving) decision to pursue acting came after seeing ‘Pirates of the Caribbean’ at age 12. “I was exported out of this world,” she says. “I was just so filled with curiosity, and I knew I wanted to be a part of whatever just happened to me. I wanted to know how to get an invitation to that party.” For our September issue, the actress talks playing a social media influencer on @9strangershulu, getting starstruck by her castmates (Nicole Kidman, Melissa McCarthy, and Michael Shannon, to name a few), and staying grounded through it all. node.text: The renaissance of the ’90s country club mom (think somewhere between Meredith Blake from #TheParentTrap and Hilary Banks from #TheFreshPrinceofBelAir) has arrived. Those born after the ’90s are embracing the look, which might involve a structured jacket paired with Prada loafers, or a Cartier Tank watch with a tennis dress. But before we jump to any conclusions about how maybe we should leave the revival to the kids, it must be noted that this particular #richmom vibe is timeless. In fact, the ’90s country club mom’s belief that one should invest in beautiful, well-made pieces and wear them again and again, allowing them to develop a beautiful patina, is the very essence of the sustainable fashion ethos we should all be trying to adopt right now. Membership to your nearest country club is not needed, but tennis lessons might be a good idea for veritas sake. Either way, shop key pieces at the link in bio.

node.text: Just like her iconic songs, Aretha Franklin’s clothing was emotional. “In a way, clothing for her was a way to express her emotions, not necessarily a personality or a sense of style,” says costume designer @ClintRamos, who worked on the newest Franklin biopic, @respectmovie. While the drama, starring Jennifer Hudson, traces the music legend’s journey of finding her voice over the course of her transcendent career, it also highlights Franklin’s underrated status as a fashion icon. “When you see a lot of photographs of Aretha wearing clothing, she’s in control of the clothing. The clothing is not wearing her,” says Ramos. “And by being in control, her humanity shows through it.” At the link in bio, Ramos breaks down the icon’s wardrobe and talks bringing it to life onscreen with @iamjhud.

Want to be the diamond of the season? You’re in luck. @NellieDiamond of @HillHouse (the brand that gave us the beloved Nap Dress) has partnered with @Phenomenal and Netflix to produce a ‘Bridgerton’-inspired capsule collection. The line, which spans three nap dresses and two bejweled hair pins, interprets Hill House Home’s greatest hits through a #regencycore lens. “When I saw ‘Bridgerton,’ I think the reason I was so excited about it was that the aesthetic is so us,” Diamond says. “I like to think that the ‘Bridgerton’ characters would like nap dresses.” Head to the link in bio to shop all the dresses that even Lady Whistledown would approve of.

node.text: Jamie Spears is officially stepping down as the conservator of #BritneySpears’ estate. The court filing to relinquish his control over his daughter’s career and estate comes after months of heightened pressure from the public and passionate fans. In the official petition, Jamie states via his attorney that he wants to avoid a “public battle with his daughter.” Previously, the pop star spoke out for the first time regarding her experience living under a conservatorship the last 13 years in an emotional 30-minute long court address. “I just want my life back,” she said. “It’s been 13 years. And it’s enough.” Read more at the link in bio.
